\begin{align*}
(2y-1)\cdot(4y^{10}+2y^9+4y^8+2y^7) &= 2y\cdot(4y^{10}) + 2y\cdot(2y^9) + 2y\cdot(4y^8) + 2y\cdot(2y^7) - 1\cdot(4y^{10}) - 1\cdot(2y^9) - 1\cdot(4y^8) - 1\cdot(2y^7) \\
&= 8y^{11} + 4y^{10} + 8y^9 + 4y^8 - 4y^{10} - 2y^9 - 4y^8 - 2y^7
\end{align*}
Now, let's combine the like terms:
\begin{align*}
8y^{11} + 4y^{10} + 8y^9 + 4y^8 - 4y^{10} - 2y^9 - 4y^8 - 2y^7 &= 8y^{11} + (4y^{10} - 4y^{10}) + (8y^9 - 2y^9) + (4y^8 - 4y^8) - 2y^7 \\
&= 8y^{11} + 6y^9 - 2y^7
\end{align*}
So, the answer is:
\begin{align*}
8y^{11} + 6y^9 - 2y^7
\end{align*}

